# ⚙️ Environment Configuration Template

> **⚠️ IMPORTANT**: Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your actual values!
> **NEVER** commit this file with real secrets to Git.

## 🔑 Required Variables

```bash
# Google Gemini API Key (REQUIRED)
GEMINI_API_KEY="your-actual-api-key-here"

# Vite Production Endpoint (optional, if using proxy)
VITE_API_ENDPOINT="http://localhost:8080/api"
```

## 🎨 Optional Variables

```bash
# Node.js Environment (dev|production|test)
NODE_ENV=production

# CORS Allowed Origins (comma-separated)
CORS_ORIGINS="http://localhost:3000,http://yoursite.com"

# Rate Limiting Configurations
RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS=100
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000

# Logging Level (debug|info|warn|error)
LOG_LEVEL=info
```

## 📝 Example `.env` File

```bash
# Real production example:
GEMINI_API_KEY="AIzaSy...your-actual-key-here"
VITE_API_ENDPOINT="http://api-service:8080"
NODE_ENV=production
CORS_ORIGINS="http://your-app-domain.com"
RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS=50
LOG_LEVEL=warn
```

## 🔒 Security Best Practices

### ✅ DO:
- Generate new API keys from [Google AI Studio](https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey)
- Rotate keys every 90 days maximum
- Use OCP Secrets for production deployments
- Set `NODE_ENV=production` in prod builds
- Keep `.env` file local and not committed to Git

### ❌ DON'T:
- Hardcode keys in source code (`vite.config.ts`)
- Commit `.env` with real credentials
- Share API keys publicly (including README files)
- Use the same key for multiple projects if possible

---

## 🚨 Quick Start

1. Copy this file:
```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

2. Edit `.env` with your values:
```bash
nano .env
# or vim/vscode
```

3. Run app (it will pick up from `.env`):
```bash
npm run dev
```

4. For production build:
```bash
# Ensure NODE_ENV=production in .env
npm run build
docker build -t ai-english-tutor:latest .
docker run -p 3000:3000 -e GEMINI_API_KEY=... ai-english-tutor:latest
```

